fg_segments: Privacy Policy Your privacy is very important to us.
Accordingly, we have developed this Policy in order for you to understand how we collect, use, communicate and disclose and make use of personal information.
The following outlines our privacy policy. By visiting or using our website, you agree to be bound to the terms stated in this Privacy Policy. What information do we collect?
We only collect personal information that allows us to provide the services you have agreed to receive.
Your business name, website and e-mail address will be requested from you when you register for an account.
This is required in order to set up an account and also for re-directing clients to your website.
We enable you to provide information when creating collection in order to personalize the gallery for your clients, you can control how this information is displayed.
We take the personal information you provided to us very seriously.

Your information, whether public or private, will not be sold, exchanged, transferred, or given to any other company for any reason whatsoever, without your consent, other than for the express purpose of delivering the services requested.
The email address you provide may be used to send you our e-mail newsletter, respond to inquiries, and/or other requests or questions.
We may also release your information when we believe release is appropriate to comply with the law, enforce our site policies, or protect ours or others rights, property, or safety.
We also receive other types of information such as "traffic data" etc. whenever you interact with the site.
We may use this information to help diagnose problems with its servers, analyze trends and administer the website.
What is this cookies thing and What is your policy regarding cookies?

Cookies are small files that a site or its service provider transfers to your computer's hard drive through your Web browser (if you allow) that enables the sites or service providers systems to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information

We do not collect any personal information through cookies however they are used for authentication and occasionally used for offering you a better site experience. You may disable cookies by adjusting your browser settings.
We may offer links to third party products or services.
These third party sites have separate and independent privacy policies.
We therefore have no responsibility or liability for the content and activities of these linked sites.
Nonetheless, we seek to protect the integrity of our site and welcome any feedback about these sites.
Please also visit our Terms of Service section establishing the use, disclaimers, and limitations of liability governing the use of our website at Terms of Service
Pixieset reserves the right to change this policy at any time by posting a revised version here.
The date of the most recent revisions will be stated on this page.
By using our website you agree to the latest version of our Privacy Policy.

Privacy Policy
Your privacy is very important to us. Accordingly, we have
developed this Policy in order for you to understand how we collect, use,
communicate and disclose and make use of personal information. The following
outlines our privacy policy. By visiting or using our website, you agree to
be bound to the terms stated in this Privacy Policy.
What information do we collect? 

We only collect personal information that allows us to provide the services you
have agreed to receive. Your business name, website and e-mail address will be
requested from you when you register for an account.  This is required in order to set up an account
and also for re-directing clients to your website. We enable you to provide
information when creating collection in order to personalize the gallery for
your clients, you can control how this information is displayed.

What do we use your information for? 

We take the personal information you provided to us very seriously. Your
information, whether public or private, will not be sold, exchanged,
transferred, or given to any other company for any reason whatsoever, without
your consent, other than for the express purpose of delivering the services requested.

The email address you provide may be used to send you our e-mail newsletter,
respond to inquiries, and/or other requests or questions. We may also release
your information when we believe release is appropriate to comply with the law,
enforce our site policies, or protect ours or others rights, property, or
safety.
We also receive other types of information such as
“traffic data” etc. whenever you interact with the site. We may use this
information to help diagnose problems with its servers, analyze trends and
administer the website.

What is this cookies thing and What is your policy regarding cookies?
Cookies are small files that a site or its service
provider transfers to your computer’s hard drive through your Web browser (if
you allow) that enables the sites or service providers systems to recognize
your browser and capture and remember certain information

We do not collect any personal information through cookies however they are
used for authentication and occasionally used for offering you a better site
experience. You may disable cookies by adjusting your browser settings. 

Third party links 

We may offer links to third party products or services. These third party sites
have separate and independent privacy policies. We therefore have no
responsibility or liability for the content and activities of these linked
sites. Nonetheless, we seek to protect the integrity of our site and welcome
any feedback about these sites.

Terms and Conditions 

Please also visit our Terms of Service section establishing the use,
disclaimers, and limitations of liability governing the use of our website at  Terms of Service

Changes to our Privacy Policy

Pixieset reserves the right to change this policy at any time by posting a
revised version here. The date of the most recent revisions will be stated on
this page.  By using our website you
agree to the latest version of our Privacy Policy. 

This policy was last modified on May 22, 2013.
